title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: Enhanced regional environment for at-scale delivery of quality, evidence-informed and innovative country programmes for the prevention and response to violence against children, and provision of care and legal protection for children in development and humanitarian contexts., which contributes to Access To Justice, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: ESAR Country Offices achieve Programming Excellence (programmes are gender and equity focused, respond to humanitarian and development contexts, deliver and demonstrate results) by 2021

description.narrative: UNICEF ESARO continued to provide regional-level leadership to ensure continuity and expansion of child protection services during the COVID-19 Pandemic and beyond. ESARO engaged partners through various regional platforms to focus on and promote UNICEF’s regional priorities areas of preventing and responding to violence against children, child marriage and female genital mutilation, civil registration and vital statistics, social service workforce strengthening, child protection in emergencies, and children on the move. A concerted focus and advancement throughout ESAR on Social Service Workforce Strengthening and child care reform led to the first ever regional partnership withUSAID Displaced Children and Orphans Fund.;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/03/2022
